Class MultiValueNullableAttribute<O,A>

All Implemented Interfaces:
Attribute<O,A>
public abstract class MultiValueNullableAttribute<O,A>
extends AbstractAttribute<O,A>

Represents an attribute in an object which has multiple values (such as a field which is itself a collection), where some of the values might be null, or where the collection of values itself might be null.

Provides a method to read the values from the field given such an object.

This type of attribute performs runtime validation of values to handle nulls, which can impact performance. When it is known that values will not be null, it is recommended to use MultiValueAttribute instead.

Author:
Niall Gallagher

MultiValueNullableAttribute

public MultiValueNullableAttribute(String attributeName,
                                   boolean componentValuesNullable)
Creates an attribute with the given name. This name is not actually used by the query engine except in providing informative exception and debug messages. As such it is recommended, but not required, that a name be provided.

A suitable name might be the name of the field to which an attribute refers.

Parameters:
attributeName - The name for this attribute
componentValuesNullable - Supply true if some of the multiple values in the list returned might be null, supply false if only the collection returned itself might be null
